            <th scope="row">Wrestling Stance</th>
            <td
              ><ul>
                <li>
                  As you move, keep your center of gravity between your legs and
                  your weight going straight down (don’t overcommit to either
                  leg)
                </li>
                <li>
                  A low stance (your head lower than your opponent’s head or at
                  the same level) is better for both offense and defense
                </li>
                <li>
                  Standing tall is mainly for when you want to bait your
                  opponent into attacking (e.g., if you’re great at defense)
                </li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Double Leg Takedown</th>
            <td
              ><ul>
                <li>
                  Breakfall: Hang onto your opponent by holding their hip with
                  your top hand and folding your chest onto their back. Soften
                  your fall by reaching far out to the ground with your other
                  arm (posting it too close to your landing spot may cause
                  injury) and then slapping the ground with the first arm.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
